The anti-radical scavenging activity of samples was evaluated based on the colorimetric method12. Briefly, 15 μL of methanolic extract was added to 2.0 mL of the 2, 2-diphenyl-1-picrylhydrazyl (DPPH) solution and the mixture was incubated in dark place at 20 °C for 30 min12. Then the absorbance was measured at 517 nm. The following equation was used to calculation of DPPH inhibition12:3\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
